# Summary
Using TryGetExtension to obtain an instance of OpenAL EffectExtension returns false.

# Steps to reproduce
- Platform: Windows 11 Desktop
- Framework Version: .NET 6.0
- API: OpenAL
- API Version: 1.1 ALSOFT 1.23.1

When I try to obtain an instance of EffectExtension using TryGetExtension, the call returns false indicating that the extension is not present.

```
AL al = AL.GetApi(true);
EffectExtension efx;
if (!al.TryGetExtension(out efx))
    throw new Exception();
```

I played around with the OpenAL Soft library and it likewise returns false when I call: `alIsExtensionPresent("ALC_EXT_EFX")`

What is the intended way to get an instance of EffectExtension? I can simply go `efx = new EffectExtension(al.Context);` but that seems inconsistent. Obtaining the effect extension context API works as expected:
```
ALContext alc = ALContext.GetApi(true);
EffectExtensionContext efxContext;
if (!alc.TryGetExtension(null, out efxContext))
    throw new Exception();
```

